    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced pepper </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>star anise</strong> and a pinch of<strong> sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
